cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with visual recognition systems and proposes a deep architecture for domain generalization, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel deep architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of aggregation modules and layer strategies could also indicate that the paper belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments involve benchmark databases, which could suggest that the paper belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
